                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="21470" author="zznate" created="Wed, 27 Dec 2006 09:56:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;A patch which goes back to the traditional WebUtils method of view name extraction.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="21544" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Mon, 1 Jan 2007 20:19:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The inconsistency between code and documentation has already been discovered and fixed for 2.0.1 (see &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-2789&quot; title=&quot;UrlFilenameViewController backward compatibility broken&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPR-2789&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPR-2789&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Note that the actual path extracted depends on the HandlerMapping&apos;s mapped path: So if you specify &quot;/foo/bar/**&quot; there, it will extract &quot;filename&quot; for the URL &quot;/foo/bar/filename.jsp&quot;. This is the recommended way to narrow the path now. In Spring 1.2, the mapped path was ignored completely, always extracting the plain filename. For a specific path mapping like the above, the behavior should be backwards-compatible; it just breaks for &quot;wide&quot; path mappings.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
